  "text": "Alternatively, the combination of microfluidics and SAXS provides also a powerful tool to investigate dynamic processes on a molecular level with a sub-millisecond time resolution. By controlling flow rates and channel volumes, time resolution can be translated to spatial resolution, which is easily exploited using focused X-ray beams. Due to a constant flow of material within the device, radiation can be controlled and acquisition times can be increased, allowing for better signal/noise ratios while maintaining temporal resolution. Recent improvements to SAXS, coupled with microfluidics devices applied to the study of biological specimens, can be found in [CITATION_1] .",
